<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="651" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Tassara</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The undersigned, Acting Secretary of State of the United States, has the
                            to inform him, in reply, that copies of the resolutions of sympathy
                            which accompanied it, adopted at a meeting of the Spanish residents of
                            New York, will pursuant to the request of Mr. Tassara, be transmitted to
                            the family of the late President and to the Secretary of State. </p>
                        <p>The undersigned offers to Mr. Tassara renewed assurances of his very high
                            consideration. </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W.HUNTER</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Señor Don <hi rend="smallcaps">Gabriel Garcia y Tassara</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., Washington.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>